{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:matthew.22",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "matthew",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22",
    "summary": "Source text for Matthew 22 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:1",
      "text": "And again Jesus spoke to them in parables, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:2",
      "text": "“The kingdom of heaven may be compared to a king who gave a marriage feast for his son,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:3",
      "text": "and sent his servants to call those who were invited to the marriage feast; but they would not come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:4",
      "text": "Again he sent other servants, saying, ‘Tell those who are invited, Behold, I have made ready my dinner, my oxen and my fat calves are killed, and everything is ready; come to the marriage feast.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:5",
      "text": "But they made light of it and went off, one to his farm, another to his business,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:6",
      "text": "while the rest seized his servants, treated them shamefully, and killed them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:7",
      "text": "The king was angry, and he sent his troops and destroyed those murderers and burned their city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:8",
      "text": "Then he said to his servants, ‘The wedding is ready, but those invited were not worthy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:9",
      "text": "Go therefore to the thoroughfares, and invite to the marriage feast as many as you find.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:10",
      "text": "And those servants went out into the streets and gathered all whom they found, both bad and good; so the wedding hall was filled with guests.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:11",
      "text": "“But when the king came in to look at the guests, he saw there a man who had no wedding garment;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:12",
      "text": "and he said to him, ‘Friend, how did you get in here without a wedding garment?’ And he was speechless.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:13",
      "text": "Then the king said to the attendants, ‘Bind him hand and foot, and cast him into the outer darkness; there men will weep and gnash their teeth.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:14",
      "text": "For many are called, but few are chosen.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:15",
      "text": "Then the Pharisees went and took counsel how to entangle him in his talk.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:16",
      "text": "And they sent their disciples to him, along with the Herodi-ans, saying, “Teacher, we know that you are true, and teach the way of God truthfully, and care for no man; for you do not regard the position of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:17",
      "text": "Tell us, then, what you think. Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:18",
      "text": "But Jesus, aware of their malice, said, “Why put me to the test, you hypocrites?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:19",
      "text": "Show me the money for the tax.” And they brought him a coin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:20",
      "text": "And Jesus said to them, “Whose likeness and inscription is this?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:21",
      "text": "They said, “Caesar's.” Then he said to them, “Render therefore to Caesar the things that are Caesar's, and to God the things that are God's.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:22",
      "text": "When they heard it, they marveled; and they left him and went away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:23",
      "text": "The same day Sadducees came to him, who say that there is no resurrection; and they asked him a question,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:24",
      "text": "saying, “Teacher, Moses said, ‘If a man dies, having no children, his brother must marry the widow, and raise up children for his brother.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:25",
      "text": "Now there were seven brothers among us; the first married, and died, and having no children left his wife to his brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:26",
      "text": "So too the second and third, down to the seventh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:27",
      "text": "After them all, the woman died.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:28",
      "text": "In the resurrection, therefore, to which of the seven will she be wife? For they all had her.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:29",
      "text": "But Jesus answered them, “You are wrong, because you know neither the scriptures nor the power of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:30",
      "text": "For in the resurrection they neither marry nor are given in marriage, but are like angels in heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:31",
      "text": "And as for the resurrection of the dead, have you not read what was said to you by God,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:32",
      "text": "‘I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob’? He is not God of the dead, but of the living.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:33",
      "text": "And when the crowd heard it, they were astonished at his teaching.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:34",
      "text": "But when the Pharisees heard that he had silenced the Sadducees, they came together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:35",
      "text": "And one of them, a lawyer, asked him a question, to test him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:36",
      "text": "“Teacher, which is the great commandment in the law?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:37",
      "text": "And he said to him, “You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your mind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:38",
      "text": "This is the great and first commandment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:39",
      "text": "And a second is like it, You shall love your neighbor as yourself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:40",
      "text": "On these two commandments depend all the law and the prophets.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:41",
      "text": "Now while the Pharisees were gathered together, Jesus asked them a question,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:42",
      "text": "saying, “What do you think of the Christ? Whose son is he?” They said to him, “The son of David.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:43",
      "text": "He said to them, “How is it then that David, inspired by the Spirit, calls him Lord, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:44",
      "text": "‘The Lord said to my Lord, Sit at my right hand, till I put thy enemies under thy feet’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:45",
      "text": "If David thus calls him Lord, how is he his son?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:matthew.22.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 22:46",
      "text": "And no one was able to answer him a word, nor from that day did any one dare to ask him any more questions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
